OL,3,C'I'm going, I'm going': Man in cardiac
OL,4,Carrest while on phone to 999
OL,6,FYorkshire Ambulance Service's
OL,7,FCommunity Engagement Manager, Jason
OL,8,FCarlyon, said: "What happens in the
OL,9,Ffirst few minutes after someone has
OL,10,Fsuffered a cardiac arrest is vital.
OL,12,F"If bystanders can call 999 and start
OL,13,FCPR while sending someone to retrieve
OL,14,Fthe nearest defibrillator, that
OL,15,Fperson's chances of survival can
OL,16,Ftriple.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/9
